OL,3,CPM faces renewed calls from parliament
OL,4,Cto pass Hillsborough Law
OL,6,FAddressing the House of Commons during
OL,7,FPrime Minister's Questions, Sir Ed
OL,8,FDavey said: "I think the whole House
OL,9,Fwill agree that the (Peter) Mandelson
OL,10,Fscandal has shown yet again why we
OL,11,Fneed a duty of candour for anyone and
OL,12,Feveryone in public office."
OL,14,FHe added: "There should be no more
OL,15,Fdelays in putting the Hillsborough Law
OL,16,Fon the statute books, after the long
OL,17,Ffight by the bereaved families and so
OL,18,Fmany others like the Mayor of Greater
OL,19,FManchester (Andy Burnham).
OL,26,@vD@KOU{D@Lpm{D@Ypn
